    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix QoS Flow Failed Item Handling in E1AP Bearer Context Management\n\n### Summary\nThe E1AP bearer context management code in the gNB was unable to properly handle QoS flow failed items in Bearer Context Setup and Modification responses. When the CU-UP included QoS flow failed lists in its responses, the gNB would hit an AssertFatal with \"not implemented\" message, causing the E1AP connection to be dropped and bearer establishment to fail.\n\nThe root cause was missing implementation for parsing and storing QoS flow failed information from ASN.1 structures. The code only handled QoS flow setup lists but completely ignored failed lists, leading to crashes when these optional IEs were present.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/COMMON/e1ap_messages_types.h`: Added `qos_flow_failed_t` structure and updated `DRB_nGRAN_setup_t`, `DRB_nGRAN_modified_t`, and `DRB_nGRAN_failed_t` structures with `numQosFlowFailed` and `qosFlowsFailed` fields to store failed QoS flow information.\n- `openair2/E1AP/e1ap.c`: Replaced AssertFatal statements with proper parsing logic for QoS flow failed lists in both `extract_BEARER_CONTEXT_SETUP_RESPONSE` and `extract_BEARER_CONTEXT_MODIFICATION_RESPONSE` functions. Added complete cause type handling for all E1AP cause categories.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure gNB with CU-CP/CU-UP split architecture\n2. Trigger PDU session establishment that results in some QoS flows failing at the CU-UP\n3. Observe that the CU-UP includes QoS flow failed items in the Bearer Context Setup Response\n4. The gNB will crash with \"not implemented\" assertion when trying to process the flow_Failed_List IE\n5. E1AP connection is dropped and PDU session establishment fails\n\nWith this fix, the gNB properly parses and stores QoS flow failed information, allowing the E1AP connection to remain stable and providing the core network with visibility into which QoS flows failed and why.\n"
}